{{Japanese name|Nakahara}}

[[File:Zen painting and calligraphy on silk signed Hachijûgo (85 year old) Nantembô Tôjû, 1923.jpg|thumb|right|100px|Painting and calligraphy on silk signed “Hachijūgo (85-year-old) Nantembō Tōjū”, 1923]]

{{nihongo|'''Nakahara Nantenbō'''|中原 南天棒||April 3, 1839 &ndash; February 12, 1925}}, also known as '''Tōjū Zenchū''' and as '''Nantenbō Tōjū''', was a [[Japanese Zen]] Master.  In his time known as a fiery reformer{{clarify|date=January 2014}}, he was also a prolific and accomplished artist.  He produced many fine examples of Zen Art and helped bridge the gap between older forms of Zen [[Buddhist art]] and its continuation in the 20th century.

